name: **Inishskinnymore – _Inis Scine Mór_**
description: Inishskinnymore – Inis Scine Mór L513-641 Sheet 37 This is the larger of two islands, midway across the south-eastern entrance to Ship Sound. Inishskinnymore is low, sheep-grazed, short-grassed, and altogether quite a pleasant 3/4 hectares. There is a lovely sandy beach on the northern side. A pebble beach in the SE has the best camping potential.
